cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.RO

This paper deals with computer vision tasks using dynamic vision sensors, which are commonly studied in the computer vision community (cs.CV). The proposed approach involves using Long Short-Term Memory (LSTM) cells to learn end-to-end event-surfaces, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of neural networks for event-based object classification, which falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper proposes a differentiable recurrent surface, which is a technique commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the use of event-based data for optical flow estimation, which is a topic commonly studied in robotics (cs.RO).
